OL,3,CPipe band honours former member who
OL,4,Cdied after D-Day eighty years ago
OL,6,FIsla Todd reports from Hawick
OL,8,FTributes have been paid to a former
OL,9,Fmember of a pipe band in Hawick, who
OL,10,Fwas killed following the D-Day
OL,11,Flandings eighty years ago.
OL,13,FWilliam 'Willie' Johnstone was the
OL,14,FPipe Major of the Hawick Scout Pipe
OL,15,FBand in the 1930s. He left the town to
OL,16,Fgo and fight in Normandy and died a
OL,17,Ffew weeks after the D-Day landings, on
OL,18,Fthe 17th of July 1944.
