OL,3,CPipe band honours former member who
OL,4,Cdied after D-Day eighty years ago
OL,6,FTo remember his life and death, Hawick
OL,7,FScout Pipe Band marched through the
OL,8,Ftown and laid a wreath at the war
OL,9,Fmemorial in his name. A young piper
OL,10,Falso played a lament on Willie's
OL,11,Fbagpipes which have been passed down
OL,12,Fto different members of the band over
OL,13,Fthe years.
OL,15,FHis wife had been pregnant with
OL,16,Fdaughter Dorothy when he was killed by
OL,17,Fa sniper in 1944.
