OL,3,CPipe band honours former member who
OL,4,Cdied after D-Day eighty years ago
OL,6,FFamously, Willie played his bagpipes
OL,7,Fas soldiers stormed the beaches at
OL,8,FNormandy. Since then the bagpipes have
OL,9,Fbeen passed down to different members
OL,10,Fof his old band over the last eight
OL,11,Fdecades.
OL,13,FThey are embossed with a plaque that
OL,14,Fsays 'Bagpipes played at the Battle of
OL,15,FNormandy by Pipe Major William
OL,16,FJohnstone, killed in action.'
